FBIS3-16511 "drsov052_s_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-052 Document Type:Daily Report 16 Mar 1994 Georgia Advadze on Abkhazia, Shevardnadze Visit to UN NC1603171294 Yerevan SNARK in English 0916 GMT 16 Mar 94 NC1603171294 Yerevan SNARK Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow, March 16 (SNARK)--"Georgia will never say "yes" to the Abkhazia's separation from Georgia. Abkhazians won the war, but it's the temporary victory", Valerian Advadze, Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary Ambassador of Georgia to Russia, told yesterday March 15 at his press-conference in Moscow. According to Valerian Advadze, the danger of separatism exists not only for Georgia but also for the other countries of the world. "The separatism in Abkhazia should be curbed, otherwise it will bring to civil wars". So, the Russian Federation should support Georgia otherwise Russia will solve the same problems. Mr. Advadze considers the visit of the Georgian leader Eduard Shevardnadze to the UN "very successful". The main aim of the visit was to convince world community of the necessity to introduce the peace-making forces into the zone of the conflict, to get the economical aid and political support of the Shevardnadze's course. [Yerevan SNARK in English at 0916 in a similarly datelined report adds: "Abkhazia is the land of Georgia. It's necessary to recognize Abkhazia as a part of the Georgian state to prevent the possible bloodshed, Valerian Advadze, Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary Ambassador of Georgia to Russia, told in his exclusive interview to SNARK. ["According to Mr. Ambassador, Abkhazia is guilty in torpedoing peace negotiations as she doesn't recognize the territorial integrity of Georgia. ["'World speaks for Georgia and the Shevardnadze's visit to the UN confirms such attitude. There doesn't exist any state which recognizes the independence of Abkhazia. Abkhazians speak against the will of the whole world community', Mr. Advadze said."]
